      "note_no": "37",
      "note": "The term la'nah - which is usually, but inexactly, translated as \"curse\" - is in its primary meaning synonymous with ib'ad (\"alienation\", \"estrangement\" or \"banishment\") in the moral sense; hence it denotes \"rejection from all that is good\" (Lisan al-'Arab) and, with reference to God, the sinner's \"exclusion from His grace\" (Manar II, 50)."
